Gunmen yesterday killed two persons and injured 10 others in an attack on Dabagi village in Tangaza Local Government Area of Sokoto State. Daily Trust learnt that the attack occurred at about 3:00am when some of the villagers were preparing for a wedding ceremony. The Police Public Relations Officer, Sokoto Command, ASP Muhammad Abubakar Sadiq, confirmed the incident. He said a group of hoodlums shot dead two youths who were among those preparing for the ceremony at that hour. He said the command found five empty shells of AK-47 rifle and one live ammunition at the scene of the attack. He said the command was making efforts to get the path taken by the hoodlums for possible tracing and arrest. 2 nabbed trying to collect N.3m ransom Bandits kill 10 in fresh Katsina attack ‘How armed bandits have been terrorising us’ Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin